#### 154. Platero and I
##### Juan Ramón Jiménez
##### lyrical · pastoral · innocence

This beautiful, deeply poetic prose collection features an exceptionally gentle, lyrical narrative style that chronicles the daily life of a writer and his small donkey in rural Spain. It is a comforting, artistic read that celebrates the simple joys, local tragedies, and deep companionship found in a white-walled Andalusian village.

Avoiding an aggressive plot, brief, impressionistic chapters follow the seasons across a single year. Vivid descriptions of local festivals, changing flowers, children at play, and the poverty of rural outcasts find profound beauty and philosophical comfort within a humble, transient world.

