#### 157. Dry Valley
##### Ivan Bunin
##### memory · gentry · ruin

This haunting, lyrical novella utilizes a dense, impressionistic prose style that explores the psychological and physical collapse of a minor noble family. It appeals to readers who appreciate gothic atmospheres, exploring inherited family trauma and the tragic obsession of a young servant girl who remains loyal to the family that destroys her.

Rejecting linear time, the story moves fluidly through memories, family legends, and ghostly encounters narrated from a generational distance. The legal and emotional legacies of serfdom continue to poison the minds of both masters and servants, turning innocent devotion into a fatalistic acceptance of a shared curse.

##### Fiction, 1912, 130 pages

