#### 158. Jean-Christophe
##### Romain Rolland
##### epic · musical · integrity

This monumental epic novel utilizes a sweeping, emotional prose style to chronicle the life of a musical genius. It is an inspiring artistic coming-of-age story that champions fierce, unyielding commitment to artistic honesty against commercial corruption and nationalistic hatred in early twentieth-century Europe.

Explicitly modeled after a musical symphony, movements track the protagonist's development from a troubled childhood in Germany to creative maturity in Paris. Artistic rivalries, political upheavals, and intense friendships test the hero's principles as he channelizes raw anger into enduring, universal art.

