#### 160. Principia Mathematica
##### Bertrand Russell
##### logical · mathematical · foundation

This monumental foundational text utilizes a highly formal, uncompromising system of symbolic logic to derive the core principles of mathematics from pure logic. It serves as an ultimate intellectual monument representing a historic peak of human rationalism and the desire for absolute certainty.

Built from the ground up using specialized symbolic notation to avoid the ambiguities of human language, the work is incredibly complex. Hundreds of pages of meticulous proofs are developed before even defining the number one, aiming to systematically eliminate paradoxes from the foundations of set theory.

