Fluid, meditative verses lack a linear narrative but follow a clear emotional arc from spiritual thirst to ecstatic realization. Simple, repetitive structures hide sophisticated philosophical concepts as the speaker's soul slowly sheds its pride and worldly anxieties to achieve a state of universal love.

