#### 167. The Long Journey
##### Johannes V. Jensen
##### mythic · anthropological · epic

This ambitious, multi-volume historical epic features a grand, imaginative narrative style that seeks to retell the history of human civilization from the pre-Ice Age to the discovery of America. Focusing on early human pioneers who invent fire, tools, and navigation, it turns human survival into an inspiring adventure.

Episodic and generational, archetypal figures drive humanity forward through major technological and evolutionary shifts. Environmental challenges—such as the sudden arrival of the Ice Age—force tribes to adapt, tracing how human psychology evolves from primitive, animalistic fear into an adventurous spirit that conquers the globe.

