#### 169. Creative Evolution
##### Henri Bergson
##### philosophical · biological · consciousness

This revolutionary philosophical text features an elegant, highly imaginative prose style that seeks to bridge the gap between biological science and spiritual metaphysics. Rejecting the view of a cold, mechanical universe, it introduces the *élan vital* to describe the universe as an ongoing, unpredictable act of creation.

Critiquing traditional evolutionary theories, the book argues that mechanistic determinism cannot explain the emergence of genuine novelty and consciousness. Relying on the concept of time experienced as a continuous, indivisible flow, it encourages a shift from rigid, mathematical analysis to an intuitive grasp of reality's fluid nature.

