Tracing the meteoric rise and self-imposed fall of Per as he attempts to build a revolutionary canal system, the story examines socio-economic and scientific currents. Despite achieving wealth and status, an existential awakening leads him to discard his worldly success in search of a quiet, authentic self in rural Jutland.

