High-stakes political intrigue of the "Great Game" functions alongside a quiet, spiritual quest for enlightenment. The intricate web of British imperial intelligence and ancient religious traditions forces Kim to balance his fierce loyalty to his master with his talent for deception, ultimately forcing him to choose his true path.

